Charlotte Nikoi was an associate director at Unicef in New York. (SAPS) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg (AP) - Unicef says the remains of a New York-based employee who was reported missing in March during a vacation in South Africa have been found.Charlotte Nikoi, a Ghanaian citizen, arrived in Cape Town on March 17 to celebrate her wedding anniversary with her family. She was reported missing on March 21 during a hike on Table Mountain.The UN children's agency on Saturday thanked South African authorities for their help in the case and requested privacy on behalf of Nikoi's family.Nikoi was an associate director for human resources at Unicef.An investigation is underway into the cause of her death.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.